  "edit": "Edit",
  "eventHelpTidalChangePosition": "Sets the tide position after the change. The rightmost column is 0, and the leftmost is 9. Accepts integers, including negative values.",
  "eventHelpBlackHoleBody": "A event commonly seen in Kongfu World. A black hole will spawn and pull all plants to the right.",
  "eventHelpBlackHoleColumns": "You can specify how many columns plants are dragged, indicating how many tiles they will be pulled to the right by the black hole.",
  "eventHelpMagicMirrorBody": "Spawns paired mirrors on the lawn. Each pair consists of an entrance and an exit, both sharing the same appearance.",
  "eventHelpMagicMirrorType": "You can change the mirror’s appearance to distinguish them. There are 3 different types of Magic Mirrors in this event.",
  "eventHelpParachuteRainBody": "Zombies will parachute in from above for a surprise attack. Commonly used for Bug Bot Imp, Lost Pilot Zombie, Bass Zombie, ZCorp Helpdesk, and more. Zombie levels follow the lawn’s level sequence.",
  "eventHelpParachuteRainLogic": "Zombies drop in batches. You can control the total number and the interval between each batch. Zombies will land randomly within the selected columns. If the total pre-drop delay is reached, any remaining zombies will spawn immediately.\nA red warning message will appear before the event starts. Entering Chinese text in the message may result in garbled characters. You can leave the zombie type empty to use this event purely for message display.",
  "eventHelpModernPortalsBody": "Spawns a fixed type of spacetime portal on the lawn, commonly seen in Modern Day and Memory Lane.\nOnly one spacetime portal can be configured per event. To have multiple portals appear simultaneously, add multiple Spacetime Portal events within the wave.",
  "eventHelpModernPortalsType": "There are many types of spacetime portals in the game. You can select a specific type and preview the spawned zombies.",
  "eventHelpModernPortalsIgnore": "When enabled, spacetime portals will still spawn even if blocked by grid items such as tombstones or surfboards.",
  "eventHelpFrostWindBody": "A common event in Frostbite Caves. Freezing wind is generated on specified rows, freezing plants into ice blocks.",
  "eventHelpFrostWindDirection": "You can set the direction of the wind (from left or right). Note that there is an interval between each wind event. To make them occur simultaneously, try adding multiple Freezing Wind events.",
  "eventHelpModifyConveyorBody": "This event allows you to modify conveyor belt plants during gameplay. Parameters are similar to the conveyor belt module. Make sure the conveyor belt module is already included in the level.",
  "eventHelpModifyConveyorAdd": "Adds new plants or tool packets to the conveyor belt. If the plant already exists, its previous data will be overwritten.",
  "eventHelpModifyConveyorRemove": "Removing does not work when the Creative Courtyard module is enabled. Instead, set the plant’s weight to 0 to achieve the same effect.",
  "eventHelpDinoBody": "A common event in Jurassic Marsh. Summons a specified dinosaur into a chosen row. The dinosaur will assist zombies in attacking.\nOnly one dinosaur can be configured per event. To have multiple dinosaurs appear simultaneously, add multiple Dino Summon events within the wave.",
  "eventHelpDinoDuration": "The duration the dinosaur stays on the lawn, measured in waves. It will leave after the time expires or after interacting with enough zombies.",
  "eventDinoTread": "Event: Dino Stomp",
  "eventDinoRun": "Event: Dino Stampede",
  "eventHelpDinoTreadBody": "Brontosaurus moves its foot into the designated area and stomps after a few seconds, dealing damage to all plants and zombies within range. It leaves a footprint lasting about 7 seconds, during which planting is not allowed in that area.",
  "eventHelpDinoTreadRowCol": "GridY represents the row, and GridXMin/GridXMax represent the column range. Both rows and columns start counting from 0. In Underwater World, rows range from 0–5 and columns from 0–9.",
  "dinoTreadRowLabel": "Row (GridY)",
  "dinoTreadColMinLabel": "Leftmost Column (GridXMin)",
  "dinoTreadColMaxLabel": "Rightmost Column (GridXMax)",
  "dinoTreadTimeIntervalLabel": "Entry Delay (TimeInterval)",
  "columnStartLabel": "Start Column (ColumnStart)",
  "columnEndLabel": "End Column (ColumnEnd)",
  "eventHelpDinoRunBody": "When triggered, dinosaurs gather across 2–3 rows. They do not use their abilities, but instead charge into the lawn, trampling plants or zombies. The number of targets they can trample depends on the dinosaur type.",
  "eventHelpDinoRunRow": "DinoRow defines the center row of the dino rush. Rows are 0-based. Underwater World supports up to 5.",
  "positionAndArea": "Position & area",
  "positionAndDuration": "Position & timing",
  "rowCol0Index": "Row/column (0-based)",
  "timeInterval": "Time interval",
  "eventHelpZombiePotionBody": "Force-spawns potions on the lawn, ignoring plants. Can be used as an alternative to grid item spawn events.",
  "eventHelpZombiePotionUsage": "Unlike the preset pools used for grid item spawning, this event forces grid items to spawn on specific tiles and displaces plants. \nNote that on lawns without tombstone spawn effects, sun textures may appear incorrectly. Use with caution.",
  "eventHelpShellBody": "Spawns atlantis seashells at specified positions. Seashells start in a closed state. When a zombie steps on a seashell, it opens, launches the zombie forward, and closes again after 10 seconds. While open, seashells can be attacked by plants and block straight-shot projectiles. Each time a seashell opens, it generates a random item, including a Plant Food, a Cuttlefish, a plant seed packet, or a Relic Imp. After being triggered by zombies 3 times, the seashell will swim toward the seed bank and replace a random seed slot with a seashell seed packet. After the seashell has been planted 3 times, the seed slot will revert to its original plant.",
  "eventHelpShellUsage": "Select a tile, then tap \"+\" to place a seashell. Lawn size varies by level: 6 rows × 10 columns in Underwater World, and 5 rows × 9 columns in other levels.",
  "eventHelpPumpkinHouseBody": "Spawns pumpkin houses at specified positions. Zombies that pass through the Pumpkin House are transformed into Pumpkin House Ghosts. Pumpkin House Ghosts have a separate health pool and can only be damaged by lobbed plants. When their health is depleted, they revert to their original zombie form. The Pumpkin House itself also has its own health and can be destroyed by concentrated fire.",
  "eventHelpPumpkinHouseUsage": "Select a tile, then tap \"+\" to place a pumpkin house. Lawn size varies by level: 6 rows × 10 columns in Underwater World, and 5 rows × 9 columns in other levels.",
  "eventHelpFairyFogBody": "Creates magic fog that covers the lawn and grants shields to zombies. Commonly used in Fairytale Forest levels. Can only be cleared by the Fairtyale Breeze event.\nHigher-tier fog grants stronger shields and increased control immunity to zombies. Tiers, from lowest to highest, are White, Blue, and Purple.",
  "eventHelpFairyFogRange": "mX and mY define the center point. mWidth and mHeight define how far the area extends to the right and downward from the center.",
  "eventHelpFairyWindBody": "Generates a continuous breeze that clears magical fog. Commonly used in Fairytale Forest levels.",
  "eventHelpFairyWindVelocity": "This event affects projectile speed while active. 1.0 = normal speed; higher values increase projectile speed.",
  "eventHelpRaidingPartyBody": "Commonly seen in Pirate Seas levels. Spawns groups of Swashbuckler Zombies in batches. TimeBetweenGroups defines the interval between each group.",
  "eventHelpRaidingPartyGroup": "Zombies per group.",
  "eventHelpRaidingPartyCount": "Total Swashbuckler Zombies spawned.",
  "eventHelpGravestoneBody": "Randomly spawns grid items during a wave (e.g., Dark Ages tombstones).",
  "eventHelpGravestoneLogic": "Selects valid tiles from the pool above to spawn grid items. The total number of grid items cannot exceed the number of available tiles, or excess spawns will fail.",
  "eventHelpGravestoneMissingAssets": "Some lawns without tombstone spawn effects may show sun textures instead. Use with caution.",
  "eventHelpBarrelWaveBody": "Spawns the three barrel types from the Memory Lane \"Barrel Crisis\" gimmick. Barrels roll in from the right and crush all plants in their path.",
  "barrelWaveHelpTypes": "Barrel types",
  "eventHelpBarrelWaveTypes": "Empty Barrel: Breaks with no effect.\nImp Barrel: Releases zombies (usually Imps) when destroyed.\nExplosive Barrel: Explodes on contact or when destroyed, damaging plants and zombies in a 3×3 area.",
  "barrelWaveHelpRows": "Row",
  "eventHelpBarrelWaveRows": "Rows are 1-based: Row 1 = top lane, Row 5/6 = bottom lane. Standard lawns: 5 rows. Underwater World lawns: 6 rows.",
  "eventHelpSchoolBusBody": "Spawns an Ice Cream Van in the specified lane. Ice Cream Van slowly enters from the right side while carrying zombies, occupying 2 lanes. Any plants run over by the van are instantly crushed.\nIf the van is displayed with Bubble Gun Imps and Lollipop Zombies (i.e. the schoolbus_special variant), they will continuously use their respective abilities while the van is moving.\nPlants like Spikeweed and Spikerock can puncture the van's tires. After its tires are punctured, the Ice Cream Van gradually slows down and enters a gliding state. After a short period of time, it comes to a stop and breaks down.",
  "schoolBusHelpRows": "Row",
  "eventHelpSchoolBusRows": "Rows are 1-based: Row 1 = top lane, Row 5/6 = bottom lane. Standard lawns: 5 rows. Underwater World lawns: 6 rows.",
  "eventHelpSchoolBusType": "Type selects the ice cream van variant. Normal (schoolbus_normal) is the standard van. Special (schoolbus_special) shows Bubble Gun Imps and Lollipop Zombies on the van; they use their abilities while the van is moving.",
  "schoolBusHelpZombies": "Zombies",
  "eventHelpSchoolBusZombies": "Ice Cream Van has its own health pool. Once destroyed, the zombies inside will exit the vehicle and continue advancing. Each zombie's level can be configured individually (Level 0 follows the lawn’s default level, which is Level 1 in Creative Courtyard).",
  "schoolBusRow": "Row",
  "schoolBusType": "Type",
  "schoolBusTypeNormal": "Normal",
  "schoolBusTypeSpecial": "Special",
  "schoolBusHitPoints": " Van health (SchoolBusHitPoints)",
  "schoolBusSpeed": "Van speed (SchoolBusSpeed)",
  "schoolBusZombies": "Contained zombies (Zombies)",
  "schoolBusZombieLevel": "Zombie level (Level)",
  "schoolBusAddZombie": "Add zombie",
  "schoolBusRowsHint": "Rows are 1-based: Row 1 = top lane, Row 5/6 = bottom lane.",
  "eventHelpThunderWaveBody": "Lightning strikes during the wave, hitting plants adjacent to other plants. Commonly used in Sky City levels. Each strike applies either a positive or negative charge to plants.",
  "thunderWaveHelpTypes": "Charge effects",
  "eventHelpThunderWaveTypes": "Two positive charges cause continuous percentage damage from an overhead energy orb.\nTwo negative charges paralyze the plant for a short duration.\nOne positive and one negative charge permanently slow the plant.\nPlants can still receive charges while affected, but no additional effects will be applied.",
  "thunderWaveHelpKillRate": "Kill rate",
  "eventHelpThunderWaveKillRate": "The chance for lightning to instantly kill a plant on hit (0.0–1.0). Anthurium is unaffected. This applies to both positive and negative lightning.",
  "thunderWaveTypePositive": "Positive",
  "thunderWaveTypeNegative": "Negative",
  "thunderWaveKillRate": "Kill rate",
  "thunderWaveKillRateHint": "Probability of killing plants on lightning strike (0.0–1.0), Anthurium is unaffected",
  "thunderWaveThunders": "Lightnings",
  "thunderWaveAddThunder": "Add lightning",
  "thunderWaveThunder": "Lightning",
