  "pvz1CopycatsModuleTitle": "Guess Who I Am",
  "pvz1CopycatsSectionParams": "Parameters",
  "pvz1CopycatsFieldZombieWeightLabel": "Zombie weight (ZombieWeight)",
  "pvz1CopycatsHelpZombieWeight": "The probability of summoning a zombie per attempt (0–1). The probability of summoning a plant is 1 minus this value.",
  "pvz1CopycatsFieldSpawnPlantLevelLabel": "Plant level (SpawnPlantLevel)",
  "pvz1CopycatsHelpSpawnPlantLevel": "The level of plants summoned by the Magic Hat.",
  "pvz1CopycatsSectionPlantBlackList": "Plant blacklist (PlantBlackList)",
  "pvz1CopycatsHelpPlantBlackList": "Each type of Magic Hat has its own plant pool. This pool is not affected by the blacklist, so modifying the blacklist has no effect.",
  "pvz1CopycatsSectionZombieWhiteList": "Zombie whitelist (ZombieWhiteList)",
  "pvz1CopycatsHelpZombieWhiteList": "Only zombies in the whitelist can be summoned by the Magic Hat.",
  "pvz1CopycatsHelpTip": "After adding this module, remember to pre-select Magic Hats in the Seed Bank or Conveyor Belt module. Long press or right-click the Magic Hat in the plant selection screen to preview the plants it can summon.",
  "pvz1CopycatsHelpOverview": "This module configures the summon behavior of Magic Hats that can be planted in the seed slots, commonly used in the Memory Lane mini-game \"Guess Who I Am\". Without this module, Magic Hats will not function properly. Different types of Magic Hat vary in sun cost and cooldown time. After being planted, a Magic Hat will transform into a random plant or zombie. Plants are selected from the Magic Hat’s own plant pool, while zombies are selected only from the whitelist. The weights of individual entries in the plant or zombie pools cannot be adjusted.",
  "pvz1CopycatsHelpFieldsTitle": "Parameter details",
  "pvz1CopycatsPlantListEmpty": "Blacklist is empty",
  "pvz1CopycatsZombieListEmpty": "Whitelist is empty",
  "pvz1CopycatsAddPlant": "Add plant to blacklist",
  "pvz1CopycatsAddZombie": "Add zombie to whitelist",
  "magicHatSpawnPreviewTitle": "Possible plants from Magic Hat",
  "magicHatSpawnPreviewEmpty": "No plants match this blacklist.",
  "pvz1PassageModuleTitle": "Portal Combat",
  "pvz1PassageSectionParams": "Portal parameters",
  "pvz1PassageHelpOverview": "This module configures PvZ1-style portals, commonly used in the Memory Lane mini-game \"Portal Combat\". Portals appear in groups and affect the movement paths of plant projectiles and zombies, and will periodically change positions. Note that portals do not affect plant targeting. Plants will not attack zombies on the other end of a portal ahead of them, and will only attack if there are zombies in their lane.",
  "pvz1PassageHelpFieldsTitle": "Parameter Overview",
  "pvz1PassageFieldGroupAmount": "Portal types (GroupAmount)",
  "pvz1PassageHelpGroupAmount": "The number of portal types that appear in the level. PvZ1-style portals have two types: square and circular. If set to 1, only square portals will appear. If set to 2, both square and circular portals will appear. If set to 3 or higher, the extra portal types will display as sun textures; these portals do not change position, but can still teleport zombies.",
  "pvz1PassageFieldPassageAmount": "Portals per type (PassageAmount)",
  "pvz1PassageHelpPassageAmount": "The number of portals within each type. For example, if set to 2, each type will have 2 portals. The total number of portals cannot exceed the number of tiles in the spawn area. If multiple valid destination portals exist within the same type, zombies will always teleport to the designated one.",
  "pvz1PassageFieldGridXMin": "Minimum spawn column (GridXMin)",
  "pvz1PassageHelpGridXMin": "The leftmost column where portals may spawn. The left boundary of this lawn is column 0, and the right boundary is column {maxIndex}. This value must be less than the maximum column value.",
